<section class="bg-[#0f172a] py-24 md:py-32 relative overflow-hidden">
  <!-- Subtle gradient background placeholder -->
  <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-gradient-to-br from-[#0f172a] via-[#1a1f35] to-[#0f172a] opacity-80"></div>

  <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-6 relative z-10">
    <h1 class="text-white font-black text-3xl md:text-5xl lg:text-6xl tracking-[-0.02em] leading-[1.1] mb-8">
      In 1984, the Thought Police weren't looking for criminals. Neither is Flock Safety&nbsp;&mdash; 99% of the plates they scan belong to people suspected of nothing.
    </h1>

    <p class="text-[#94a3b8] font-medium text-lg md:text-xl mb-6 leading-relaxed">
      155 cameras are watching Upstate South Carolina right now. Every car that passes gets photographed. That data goes into a national network. And nobody voted on any of it.
    </p>

    <p class="text-[#cbd5e1] text-base md:text-lg mb-10 leading-relaxed max-w-3xl">
      Your local police didn't build this alone. Flock Safety connects every camera to a national network. Agencies from other states, including federal authorities, can search it without asking you or your city. Your police can't shut that door. And neither can you.
    </p>

    <a href="#take-action" class="inline-block bg-[#dc2626] hover:bg-[#b91c1c] text-white font-bold text-sm uppercase tracking-[0.05em] px-8 py-4 rounded transition-colors">
      Email Your Legislators
    </a>
  </div>
</section>
